# Linear issue status

Applies when work maps to a **Linear** issue (e.g. **DEV-###**) on the **Development** team.

Workspace owner for handoff comments: **@brian** (`displayName` in Linear; use `list_users` with `query` if unsure).

## Always update the ticket

For the issue you are working on, **update Linear status in the same session** at each lifecycle step. Use the Linear MCP (`save_issue`) when available; otherwise update in the Linear UI. Do not finish substantive work on a mapped ticket without confirming status is current.

| When | Linear `state` |
|------|----------------|
| Starting implementation | **In Progress** (from **Todo** if applicable) |
| PR open on GitHub | **Needs Review** |
| PR merged or closed | **Done** |
| Coding before first PR | **In Progress** |

Exact state names: **Needs Review** and **Done** (not “Needs review”). Do not set **Needs Review** until a PR exists.

## GitHub PR alignment

1. **Open PR** — If a GitHub PR exists for the branch/ticket and is **open** (`gh pr view`, `state: OPEN`), set the Linear issue to **Needs Review** (unless you are actively coding before the first PR: **In Progress** is fine until the PR exists; once the PR is opened, move to **Needs Review**).
2. **PR merged or closed** — If the PR is **merged** or **closed** (any non-open terminal state), set the Linear issue to **Done**.
3. **No PR yet** — Keep **In Progress** (or **Todo** if not started).
4. **After push/PR** — When following `.cursor/rules/git-push-and-pr.mdc`, if a PR was created or merged for a **DEV-###** ticket, **update Linear in the same session** when the Linear MCP is available.

## Validation handoff comments

When you finish a **coherent chunk of work** on a mapped ticket (implementation done, PR opened, or blocked waiting on human testing), post a **top-level comment** on that issue via Linear MCP **`save_comment`** (`issueId`: `DEV-###` or issue UUID).

- **Always @brian** at the start of the comment (e.g. `@brian — …`) so he gets notified.
- Summarize **what you changed** in one short line, then **next actions for testing/validation** as a checklist: commands to run, URLs to open, flows to click, env/deploy steps, expected outcomes.
- Mirror the spirit of `.cursor/rules/change-summary-format.mdc` (**What changed** / **How to verify**) but written for the ticket thread, not only the chat reply.
- Post **in the same session** as the status update (after PR open → with **Needs Review**; before asking Brian to test manually in chat).
- Do **not** duplicate: if you already posted an equivalent handoff comment this session, update that comment (`save_comment` with `id`) instead of spamming new threads.
- If Linear MCP is unavailable, say so in chat and paste the same handoff text there.

Example body:

```markdown
@brian — ready for validation on DEV-123.

**What changed**
- Short bullet summary

**How to verify**
- [ ] Run `pnpm run build:web`
- [ ] Open … and expect …
```

## Quick check

Run `gh pr list --state all --search "DEV-NNN"` (or list by head branch) and align the linked issue’s status with the PR state above.
